  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency WASH and Food Security Intervention to Reduce Malnutrition in East Pokot</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">A) Rehabilitation and protection of temporary (dams) water sources in the area to increase water availability and increase access to cash through cash for work B)Training of water management committees to ensure proper maintenance of the water points C) Hygiene promotion in households and schools to equip target beneficiaries with the knowledge and tools to effectively combat water borne diseases D) hygiene kit distribution since the population is dependent on dam water and hence need the use of ceramic filters. E) Constructing latrines in 16 schools and training school management comittees F) Economic asset development for 3 Women community-based organizations (CBOs) by setting up a hygiene supplies store for them.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To reduce malnutrition rates in the targeted area through providing improved access to WASH and Food Security</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Whole population</narrative>
  </description>
